node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text:
Matt Robinson of @realfoodbydad has been making the most of the warm summer weather by grilling pizza in the great outdoors! With just a few high-quality ingredients like fresh produce, @BelGioiosoCheese, and our ‘00’ Pizza Flour, Matt’s serving up grilled pizza with fresh mozzarella and dollops of herbaceous pesto.
Using our Neapolitan-Style Pizza recipe and pizza grilling techniques shared in our recent Grilled Pizza video (find both at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking) you can follow along with Matt as he prepares the perfect summertime dinner.

Matt’s “Green Goddess” Pesto:
In a food processor or blender, blend a handful each of basil, arugula, and spinach with 4 garlic cloves, 1/4 cup pumpkin seeds, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, and 1/2 teaspoon salt while drizzling in 1/4 cup olive oil until smooth.

Matt’s Basic Tomato Sauce:
Pulsing a food processor or blender, combine one 28oz can whole, peeled tomatoes (preferably San Marzano), with 1 1/2 teaspoons fine sea salt. Add 2 fresh plum tomatoes for additional body, pulsing in 1 to 2-second bursts until the tomatoes are broken down.

node.text: We eat with our eyes first, and with striking two-toned pasta, Hetal Vasavada @milkandcardamom has created a true feast for the eyes! Using natural ingredients like beets, spinach, turmeric, carrots, and more, she’s here to show you how to create a rainbow of color in your next dish of homemade pasta. node.text:
Boldly spiced and slightly sweet, this is everything you love about carrot cake bundled into a quick bread with no added sugar — thanks to our Baking Sugar Alternative!

Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for this and other recipes that lean on flavorful fruits, natural sweeteners, and our Baking Sugar Alternative for the bulk of their sweetness in our Sweet Not Sugary recipe collection. Share your summer bakes with #KingArthurBaking

No cake pans? No problem! Pancakes (especially confetti 🎉 pancakes!) make for an exceptionally festive birthday cake when layered with sweetened whipped cream and maple glaze.
Make your own with our new “just-add-water” Confetti Pancake Mix. Grab a bag and find our recipe for Birthday Pancake Cake at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Show off yours with #KingArthurBaking
